						               													<description>Spangle is a deduction game for 4-10 players that can be played with a Series: Shibumi set. It uses a 4&amp;times;4 set of stacking spheres in 3 colors.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The players are members of a family who are decorating their new house. The winner is the player or players who have succeeded in decorating most of the house with the color of their choice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the end of the game, when the thirtieth ball is placed on top of the pyramid, count the balls left in the sack. The color that has the fewest balls left in the sack is the winning color and any player that chose this color at the beginning of the game wins. In case of a tie between colors, count the number of players that have chosen each color. The winning group is the one that has the fewest members. In case of another tie, both group win.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
